BANG!! BANG!! BANG!! BANG!!  <br>
</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The tall man banged on the door of the small yellow house in North Qeynos’ residential district. <br>
<br>
“Open the door! Open the door you damn Gnomes!” <br>
<br>
Just on the other side of the door, the small Gnome apothecary who goes by the name of Maladominus Foxpunter (his last name just an alias) peeked out the spyhole of the small wooden door. Judging from the voice of the Human outside, the Gnome already knew who his visitor was. <br>
<br>
As the door slowly opened, the bearded human’s figure was revealed before the door, a lanky but tall figure for a human, the Tax Collector of Qeynos known as Magistrate Ivantor Fendersin peered down upon the owner of the yellow house. <br>
<br>
“And a good day to you too Sir, now please be as certain to explain yer a’brutish bangin on my door! I did not remember ta invite some guest to me house this mornin, did I?” <br>
<br>
“You know damn well why I’m here, shortling! Don’t play around with me, it’s tax week! Now let’s make this quick and painless, you have the tax bill, and you know how much taxes you owe me. Pay up! Just why the hell Antonius Bayle decided to allow filthy Gnomes to reside in Qeynos, I have no idea! Pay up dammit!” the Human bellowed, his raspy and loud tone not settling down for one moment. <br>
<br>
Maladominus squinted for a brief moment, peering and studing his intrusive guest as he tought of his next response. <br>
<br>
“Very well, I am quite ready to pay my dues..... but do tell me, why have you not followed up on my request to empave that southern road along the Arena border? This project is long overdue, and I am not the only one to have demanded this. You know very well that the steep craggy roads as they are right now are no means for a Gnome to travel on foot! How dare you demand my taxes when you cannot deliver such basic necessities!” <br>
<br>
“What!? That road is not priority! Antonius Bayle has better things to spend his money on. And besides, why would you want that road anyways? Only the hoodlums and an occasional troublemaker from that demon-worshipping Blood Sabres cult will even venture into that ghetto district!” <br>
<br>
The Human leaned forward, and with one fist grasped the collar of the small man, almost lifting his diminutive body from the ground, “So tell me shortling, do I sense that you have something to do with those criminals in the Blood Sabres, eh?” <br>
<br>
Maladominus eyes glared, seething gaze fixed upon the man who handled him, “Put me down. Now.” <br>
<br>
The man slowly released his small-statured subject, as if somehow cowed momentarily by the stern gaze of the little Gnomish resident....yet his attitude did not let up. <br>
<br>
“I’m not leaving until I have my money. Your taxes are four days overdue, and the interest accrued....” he was quickly handed a large brown envelope mid-sentence. <br>
<br>
“It’s all in there, past dues included. Your tax bill and the coins, all there” answered the Gnome. <br>
<br>
The Human’s composure suddenly changed, as if the delivery of money had suddenly made him a changed man. He quickly tore open the enclosing flap of the envelope, just to make sure that he was dealing with an honest citizen of Qeynos. <br>
<br>
“ahhhh.... mmmm.... good.... good.... tax bill..... 3pp and 8gp coins and..... what the devil?! There’s a bit of some white powdery stuff inside the envelope!”<br>
<br>
The Gnome responded with an innocent look “What white powdery ka-bishbosh are you talkin about?” <br>
<br>
The man had quickly accrued some white powdery substance that stuck to his fingers, and he quickly wiped it on the sides of his shirt. The Gnome stepped back just a wee bit so as to avoid contact with the Tax Magistrate. <br>
<br>
“Ohhhh that stuff!” responded the little Gnome man with a sly grin, “it’s nothing really, just a little bit of talcum powder I use ta rub me hands before and after experiments. You know us Gnomes, we gotta have them smooth fingers for the Tinkerin tickety tocky! Nothing beats a little rub o’ the talcum powder!” <br>
<br>
The human responded not so politely “Smooth fingers my ass! That’s probably a good way of saying that you’re all just a bunch of shortling crooks, you damn thieves! Well, no matter, I have my payment now. Next time, you had better not make me wait again, shortling.” <br>
<br>
Maladominus smiled ear to ear, “Yes Sir, Magistrate. Let’s you and me hope there will be a next time.” <br>
<br>
The tax collector walked off as the small man closed the door. <br>
